                <note rend="inline" type="source">763.72119P43/856: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Commission to Negotiate Peace</gloss>
                        to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-12-05T12:00:00+00:00"
                            >December 5, 1919—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 6 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>5557. For the Secretary of State from Polk: Your 3942 [<hi rend="italic"
                        >3941</hi>], December 2, 4 p.m. Arrangements have been made with General
                    Connor for holding the <hi rend="italic">America</hi>. Mission will leave Paris
                    in accordance with your instructions on the evening of the 9th, and we hope to
                    sail from Brest on the 10th. Polk.</p>
                <closer>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Mission</hi>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
